diagram_notes.content:
# Running This Story

This Story is called through a Send To Story Action, which passes through either the `story_id` of the Story to backed up, or the keyword `all` which will backup all Stories.

# Export The Story

Once the list of Stories has been received, the Tines Export Story API is used to export the Story as JSON.

# Committing the Exports

The file blob tree is pushed to GitHub. This tells GitHub how to organise the file blobs created earlier.

After this is pushed, the tree is committed in a single commit message and a push request is sent to GitHub.

https://www.tines.com/api/story-library/thumbnail/87728

Exports stories to Github. The story features a form that can be used ad hoc to backup stories.

The Send to Story Action can be scheduled to run routine story backups.

Individual stories can be backed up by using their Story ID, or the argument 'all' for Story ID will backup all stories that can be accessed.

Backups are stored in folders named for their reference slug and the Team ID they are present in.

# **Requirements**

## **Credentials:**
 - [ ] `github` - GitHub OAuth app with the scope:
    - `repo user`
 - [ ] `tines_user_token` - Tines personal API token

## **Resources:**
 - [ ] `tines_api_email` - Email associated with the Tines user token
 - [ ] `github_repo` - GitHub repository name
 - [ ] `github_repo_owner` - GitHub username of repository owner

# Building the GitHub Tree

File blobs are created for each story in GitHub. A leaf is then created for each file blob which includes it's location in the repository. Each export and README file have their own blobs and leafs.

These leafs are then imploded into an array to create a file directory tree.
